Insurance companies depend on the insurance price and the amount of compensation for the customer's health status and if they believe that the risk is excessive, they simply do not make the contract.
They previously sent the customer to medical control and signed the contract with him already knowing the result of the check.
Dick ten years ago invented a much cheaper procedure: with the customer identification number, he easily obtained the list of medicines purchased in the last year and half, and the program itself draws the conclusion on the client's diseases and health status.
